Data:

How you store and lookup data has changed.
hiera_* functions are deprecated in favour of `lookup()` functions. 
lookups() should not be used in class params 
Modules can now have their own independent hierarchy
Puppet has more Data types and built-in data validation

Ruby:
Puppet DSL has evolved to support ruby-esq syntax. loops, string transformation, hash and arrays manipulation, and others. Puppet now uses ruby 2.7.

PDK:
Puppet development toolkit is a toolset to develop and test puppet module.

Facter:
Facter 4 has been introduced and how you interact with facts has changed. 
Facts have been abused and is one of the main causes for slow puppet runs. We are introducing strong rules around facts.
